The paper presents a new approximate inference method that combines Renyi $\alpha$-divergence variational inference and rejection sampling. This method is applicable to a wide range of problems in machine learning and statistics, including generative modeling, density estimation, and Bayesian inference. The paper includes experiments on synthetic and real datasets, demonstrating the efficacy of the proposed method. Given the focus on machine learning and statistics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
